ort ship]] was bombed and sunk at [[Novorossiysk]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Pipestone County||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Design 1022 ship|Design 1022 cargo ship]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean {{convert|475|nmi|km}} east of Cape Henry, [[Virginia]] ({{coord|37|43|N|66|16|W}}) by {{GS|U-576||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All 46 crew were rescued by {{USCGC|Calypso|WPG-104|6}} ({{navy|United States|coast guard}}), the fishing vessel ''Irene and May'' ({{flag|United States|1912}}) and {{SS|Tropic Star||2}} ({{flag|Norway}}).<ref name=PC>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1558.html |title=Pipestone County |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=9 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|West Imboden||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[Design 1013 ship|Design 1013 cargo ship]] was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean {{convert|175|nmi|km}} east of the ''[[United States lightship Nantucket (LV-112)|Nantucket Lightship]]'' ({{navy|USA|coast guard}}) ({{coord|41|14|N|65|55|W}}) by {{GS|U-752||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}). All 35 crew were rescued by {{USS|Bristol|DD-453|6}} ({{navy|USA|1912}}).<ref name=WI>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1559.html |title=West Imboden |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=18 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German submarine chaser|13V2  Delpa II||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[submarine chaser]] was shelled and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] ott [[Taranto]] by {{HMS|Torbay|N79|6}} ({{Navy|UK}}).<ref name=seekrieg194204/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==22 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 April 1942 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Blankenese|1929|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Barents Sea