acuse]], Italy ({{coord|37|05|N|15|41|E}}).<ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=5603468|shipname=Ninetto G. |accessdate=20 August 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Russian trawler|RT-61||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[naval trawler]] was bombed and sunk at [[Murmansk]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Soli||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker was bombed and damaged at [[Columbo]], [[Ceylon]] by [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] aircraft. She was declared a total loss and beached. She was refloated on 4 January 1952 and subsequently scrapped at [[Karachi]], Pakistan.<ref name=Soli>{{cite web |url=http://www.warsailors.com/singleships/soli.html |title=D/T Soli |publisher=Warsailors |accessdate=7 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{HMS|Tenedos|H04|6}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=World War II: The {{sclass2-|S|destroyer|||1917}} was bombed and sunk at Colombo by Japanese aircraft with the loss of 33 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Washingtonian|1919|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedord and sunk in the Indian Ocean by {{Jsub|I-5||2}} ({{navy|Empire of Japan}}).<ref name=seekrieg194204/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==6 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=6 April 1942 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Autolycus|1922|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: [[Indian Ocean Raid|Operation C]]: The cargo ship was shelled and sunk in the [[Bay of Bengal]]  {{coord|19|53|N|86|30|E}}) by {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Kumano||2}} and {{ship|Japanese cruiser|Suzuya|1934|2}} and {{ship|Japanese destroyer|Shirakumo|1927|2}} (all ({{navy|Empire of Japan}})). 17 crewmen killed.<ref name=\"combinedfleet.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.combinedfleet.com/Kumano_t.htm |title=Imperial cruisers |publisher=Combinedfleet.com |accessdate=6 April 201