ag|Sweden}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship sank by magnetic mine in the [[North Sea]] off [[Lowestoft]], [[Suffolk]], United Kingdom.<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{USS|YAG-4}} \n|flag={{navy|USA|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The auxiliary minesweeper/patrol ship was shelled and sunk by the Japanese {{convert|500|yd|m}} off Corrigidor in South Harbor.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shipscribe.com/usnaux/YAG/YAG02.html |title=US Navy Auxiliary Ships: Small YAGs acquired July-December 1941|publisher=shipscribe.com |accessdate=15 September 2014}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==13 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=13 April 1942 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Atlas|1927|2}} \n|flag={{flagcountry|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Benghazi]], [[Italian Libya|Libya]] by {{HMS|Thrasher|N37|6}} ({{navy|UK}}).<ref name=NH041242/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|HMT|Coral}} \n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[naval trawler]] was bombed and sunk at Malta.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/6334.html|title=Anti-submarine Trawler HMS Coral|publisher=Uboat|accessdate=18 November 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|El Occidente||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Panama}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy QP 10]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Barents Sea]] ({{coord|73|28|N|38|30|E}}) by {{GS|U-435||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 20 of her 41 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMS|Speedwell|J87|6}} ({{navy|United Kingdom}}).\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Empire Amethyst||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The tanker was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Caribbean Sea]] between [[Jamaica]] and [[Haiti]] ({{coord|17|40|N|74|50|W}}) by {{GS|U-154|1941|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of all 47 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Empire Progress||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] south of [[Cape Race]], [[Dominion of Newfoundland|Newfoundland]] ({{coord|40|29|N|52|35|W}}) by {{GS|U-402||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 12 of her 50 crew. Survivors were rescued by {{MV|Olaf Fostenes||2}} ({{flag|Norway}}).<ref name=Ships/><ref name=EP>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1530.html |title=Empire Progress |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=20 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Harpalion||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy QP 10]]: The cargo ship was bombed and damaged in the Barents Sea by ''Luftwaffe'' [[Junkers Ju 88]] aircraft of III ''Staffeln'', [[Kampfgeschwader 30]], [[Luftwaffe]] and was abandoned by her 70 crew. She was later torpedoed and sunk ({{coord|73|33|N|27|19|E}}) by {{GS|U-435||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}).<ref name=seekrieg194204/><ref name=Harpalion>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1531.html |title=Harpalion |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Kiev|1917|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Convoy QP 10]]: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Barents Sea ({{coord|73|22|N|28|48|E}}) by {{GS|U-436||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of six crew. Survivors were rescued by {{HMT|Blackfly|FY117|6}} ({{navy|United Kingdom}}).<ref name=Kiev>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1532.html |title=Kiev |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=25 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Korsholm||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Sweden}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean {{convert|70|nmi|km}} off [[Cape Canaveral, Florida]] by {{GS|U-123|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of nine of her 17 crew.<ref name=Korsholm>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1529.html |title=Korsholm |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=24 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Leslie|1919|2}} \n|flag={{Flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean off Cape Canaveral by {{GS|U-123|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of four of her 32 crew. One survivor was rescued by {{SS|Esso Bayonne||2}} ({{flag|United States|1912}}), the rest reached land in their lifeboats. ''Leslie'' was raised and scrapped in August 1954.<ref name=Leslie>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1528.html |title=Leslie |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=24 February 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship= {{ship|HMT|Lord Snowden}}\n|flag={{navy|United Kingdom}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[naval trawler]] was sunk in a collision off Falmouth.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/warships/ship/6411.html |title=Anti-submarine Trawler HMS Lord Snowden|publisher=Uboat |accessdate=13 April 2013}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|German landing craft|PiLB 210||2}}  \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The PiLB 40 type landing craft was lost on this date.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navypedia.org/ships/germany/ger_amph_pilb40.htm |title=PiBL 40 type landing craft, Germany |publisher=Navypedia |accessdate=6 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet motor sailer|Partizan Zheleznay||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The motor sailer was sunk by mines in the [[Kerch Gulf]]. Her [[Sea captain|Master]] and five crewmen were killed.<ref name=\"Shipnostalgia.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.shipsnostalgia.com/guides/Soviet_Merchant_Marine_Losses_in_WW2_%28Black_Sea%29|title=Soviet Marine Losses in WWII (Black Sea) |publisher=Shipnostalgia.com |accessdate=13 April 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Ryujin Maru||2}} \n|flag={{Flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Pacific Ocean]] south west of [[Shikoku]] by {{USS|Grayling|SS-209|6}} ({{navy|United States}}).<ref name=Grayling>{{cite DANFS |title=Grayling |url= http://www.hazegray.org/danfs/submar/ss209.txt |accessdate=31 December 2011 }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==14 April==\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 April 1942 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Benwood||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=[[File:Benwood-28.JPG|thumb|right|The wreck of ''Benwood'' on 23 February 2010]]The [[cargo ship]] slid off [[Alligator Reef]] \u2013 where she had grounded after colliding with {{SS|Robert C. Tuttle||2}} ({{flag|United States|1912}}) in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] northeast of [[Molasses Reef]], [[Florida]], on 9 April 1942 \u2013 and sank.<ref name=RCT/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Chekov||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=[[World War II]]: The [[transport ship]] struck a [[naval mine|mine]] and sank in the [[Black Sea]] off [[Kerch]].<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Empire Thrush||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was [[torpedo]]ed and sunk in [[Chesapeake Bay]], United States ({{coord|35|08|N|75|18|W}}) by {{GS|U-203||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) All 55 crew were rescued by {{USS|Asterion|AK-100|6}} ({{navy|United States}}).<ref name=Ships/><ref name=ET>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1537.html |title=Empire Thrush |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=9 March 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Korthion||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean south of [[Barbados]] ({{coord|12|50|N|60|30|W}}) by {{GS|U-66|1940|2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of 14 of her 23 crew.<ref name=Korthion>{{cite web |url=http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1535.html |title=Korthion |publisher=Uboat |date=16 February 2011}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet minesweper|KT-608||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[minesweeper]] struck a mine and sank in the Black Sea off Kerch.<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Lancaster Castle|1937|2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was bombed and sunk at [[Murmansk]], [[Soviet Union]] by [[Luftwaffe]] aircraft.<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''[[USS Margaret (ID-2510)|Margaret]]'' \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=World War II: The cargo ship was torpedoed and sunk in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] off [[Cape Cod]], [[Massachusetts]] by {{GS|U-571||2}} ({{navy|Nazi Germany}}) with the loss of all 29 crew.<ref name=Margaret>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/allies/merchants/ships/1536.html |title=Margaret |publisher=Uboat |accessdate=9 April 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Soviet minesweeper|SKA-042||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Soviet Union}}\n|desc=World War II: The minesweeper struck a mine and sank in the Black Sea off Kerch.<ref name=seekrieg194204/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-85|1941|2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: [[Operation Drumbeat]]: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIB submarine]] was shelled, depth charged and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean off the [[Bodie Island Light]]house ({{coord|33|55|N|75|13|W}}) by {{USS|Roper|DD-147|6}} ({{navy|United States|1912}} with the loss of all 29 crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{GS|U-252||2}} \n|flag={{navy|Nazi Germany}}\n|desc=World War II: The [[German Type VII submarine|Type VIIC submarine]] was depth charged and sunk in the Atlantic Ocean south west of Ireland ({{coord|47|00|N|18|14|W}}) by {{HMS|Stork|L81|6}} and {{HMS|Vetch|K132|6}} (both {{navy|United Kingdom}}) with the loss of all 44 crew.<ref name=U252>{{cite web |url= http://uboat.net/boats/u252.htm |title=U-252 |publi